SIMPLE: desalt
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: desalt
<hw>desalt</hw> <pos>v.</pos> <def>to remove the salt from (a solution
of salt).</def> <note>This term is used in a more general sense than
<er>desalinate</er>, which usually refers to the removal of common salt
(sodium chloride) from a water solution, such as sea water.
<ex>Desalt</ex> is commonly used to refer to any laboratory or
industrial process in which any salt may be removed from a mixture of
substances dssolved in a solvent, usually water. It is thus used as a
method of purification in chemical processes. The methods for desalting
are very varied.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> desalinate, desalinize.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>descale</ent>⟦br⟧
